
'''* Documentary by Annie Leonard: The Story of Electronics.'''

Video via http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sW_7i6T_H78&feature=player_embedded


=Description=

"Annie Leonard's animated video, The Story of Electronics, addresses a disturbing trend in electronics manufacturing which she calls 'designing for the dump'. The theory behind this concept is that manufacturers are purposefully producing electronic goods that break easily so that consumers will throw them away after minimal usage in order to buy the newer 'more improved' model. One of the many problems associated with this practice is that the electronic goods are often filled with toxic substances and improperly disposed of, causing toxic waste to build up on our planet at an alarming rate.

Thankfully, some electronics designers have started moving away from the toxins and more towards sustainable production methods. As mentioned in the video, however, we still have a long way to go. Annie Leonard concluded this segment by urging consumers to demand stronger laws on toxic substances and on banning e-waste export to developing countries. After all, it's the access to information and entertainment that we're after, not the toxic waste!"
(http://stylishorganicfamilyliving.blogspot.fr/2012/09/annie-leonards-story-of-electronics.html)


